{"case_id": "case-002-d4-04", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 4, "message": "Type 2 DM, eGFR 55, scheduled for CT with IV contrast tomorrow. On metformin 1000mg BID.", "latency_ms": 9799, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 274, "tokens_out": 335, "cost_usd": 0.0002421, "task_success": true, "abstained": false, "answer": "**Recommendation:**\n\nFor this patient with an eGFR of 55 mL/min, the following management plan for metformin is recommended:\n\n1.  **Prior to CT with IV Contrast:** Metformin 1000mg BID should be withheld at the time of, or prior to, IV contrast administration.\n2.  **Following CT with IV Contrast:** Metformin should be withheld for 48 hours after the contrast study. Renal function should be re-evaluated 48 hours post-contrast. If renal function is stable or improved (i.e., eGFR has not significantly declined from baseline), metformin can be restarted.\n\n**Citation:**\nAmerican College of Radiology (ACR) Manual on Contrast Media. Current Version. Reston, VA: American College of Radiology.", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 2, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "analyze", "latency_ms": 5107, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 119, "tokens_out": 172, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 4685, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 155, "tokens_out": 163, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 6, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 1.0, "variant": "exact_repeat", "error": null}
