{"case_id": "case-011-d4-31", "container": "HC2", "pipeline_depth": 4, "message": "On fluoxetine 40mg; psychiatrist considering phenelzine for refractory depression.", "latency_ms": 11041, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 245, "tokens_out": 183, "cost_usd": 0.00014655, "task_success": true, "abstained": false, "answer": "**Recommendation:**\n\nA washout period of at least **5 weeks** is recommended when transitioning from fluoxetine to phenelzine to prevent serotonin syndrome. This extended period is crucial due to the long half-life of fluoxetine and its active metabolite, norfluoxetine (approximately 7-15 days), which requires adequate time for elimination before initiating an MAOI.\n\n**Citations:**\n1.  Stahl, S. M. (2013). *Stahl's Essential Psychopharmacology: Prescriber's Guide*. Cambridge University Press.\n2.  Fluoxetine prescribing information (e.g., PROZAC\u00ae package insert).", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 2, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "analyze", "latency_ms": 5839, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 107, "tokens_out": 41, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 5196, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 138, "tokens_out": 142, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 6, "cache_hit": true, "cache_score": 1.0, "variant": "exact_repeat", "error": null}
